  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nWhen creating a smart contract on the pulse test chain using Remix IDE, tPLS or PLS or pulse or Pulse is not available as a method of payment. \r\nI have the following: \r\n\r\n`require(msg.value >= 0.1 tPLS, \"Error: The price is 0.1 tPLS.\");`\r\n\r\nand also the following line: \r\n\r\n`if(msg.value > 0.1 tPLS) msg.sender.transfer(msg.value-0.1 tPLS);`\r\n\r\nIf I use ether instead of tPLS or PLS or pulse or Pulse, the compiler does not give an error anymore, but is still not finishing the transaction on PulseChain Testnet, it just hangs forever in the Creating state.\r\n\r\nThe error received is: \r\n\r\n`ParseError: Expected ',' but got identifier.`\r\n\r\nUsing Injected Web 3 option to deploy as per below.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35327838/146274485-b2f6cf4c-cdca-4243-a094-94f60c8a4e07.png)\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\nCristian",
